I want to thank all the Members who helped draft this strong, bipartisan reform bill including @RepSpeier, @RepComstock, @GreggHarper, @SusanWBrooks, & @RepBrady.

From the start, my goal has been to pursue a process that holds Members of Congress to the same standard as the rest of the country when it comes to allegations of sexual harassment. There should be no special treatment.
Additionally, transparency will be increased to make sure the American people are aware when a sexual harassment claim is settled by a Congressional office.

Importantly, our reform bill will ensure taxpayers are not left to foot the bill when a Member of Congress settles a sexual harassment claim or is required to pay an award. The Member will be personally responsible going forward.

Proud to have played a role in drafting a bill to reform the way sexual harassment claims are handled on Capitol Hill. These reforms protect employees, ensure transparency, hold Members accountable, and strengthens the process. Read our full bill here: https://t.co/ypTmJ8gizF
